           <h5 class="card-title text-align: right;">Ingredients<br>Barbecue sauce</h5>
           <li>2 jalapeno peppers, finely chopped</li>
           <li>2 tbsp vegetable oil</li>
           <li>4 garlic cloves, finely chopped</li>
           <li>1 tbsp chilli powder</li>
           <li>2 tsp ground cumin</li>
           <li>1 tsp cayenne pepper</li>
           <li>2 tsp ground coriander</li>
           <li>2 cups ketchup</li>
           <li>3/4 cup fresh lime juice</li>
           <li>1/4 cup brown sugar</li>
           <li>1/2 cup of water</li>
           <li>4 lbs. pork baby back ribs</li>
           <br>
           <h5 class="card-title text-align: right;">Preparation</h5>
           <p class="card-text"> Place jalapeños, oil and garlic into a (2-qt./1.9-L) Saucepan. 
             Cook over medium heat 2-3 minutes or until fragrant. Add chili powder, cumin, cayenne pepper and coriander; cook 1 minute or until fragrant.
              Stir in ketchup, 1/4 lime juice and brown Sugar. Cover, bring to a simmer and remove from heat.<br><br>
              Cover and refrigerate some of the sauce for serving. Combine the remaining barbecue sauce, 1/2 lemon juice and water; 
              pour over baby back ribs in large shallow dish. Put them to marinate in the fridge for 2 hours.<br><br>
              Heat oven to 350°F. Remove the baby back ribs from the marinade and discard the marinade. 
              Put the baby back ribs in a shallow pan lined with aluminum foil. Bake the ribs at a low temperature (275°F) for 2 ½ to 4 hours or until they are tender.  
              <br><br>Optional: heat grill on medium-high heat for last few minutes. 
              Remove ribs from pan. Put them on the grill. Grill 10 min. per side or until cooked through,
               basting frequently with remaining sauce. Enjoy!.</p>
           
