               <h5 class="card-title text-align: right;">Ingredients</h5>
               <li>2 pounds of pork loin</li>
               <li>3 guajillo chilies</li>
               <li>1 achiote bar</li>
               <li>1/4 white onions</li>
               <li>2 garlics</li>
               <li>1/2 cups vinegar</li>
               <li>1/2 cups orange juice</li>
               <li>1 1/2 tbsp dried oregano</li>
               <li>salt</li>
               <li>black pepper</li>
               <li>1/4 cups soy sauce</li>
               <li>1/2 pineapple in small cubes</li>
               <li>1 onion filleted</li>
               <li>1 spring of fresh coriander</li>
               
               <br>
               <h5 class="card-title text-align: right;">Preparation</h5>
               <p class="card-text">Take your pork loin and cut it into pieces, and place it in a clean container, add salt, pepper, 
                 soy sauce and if you can a little garlic powder, this is optional, and let it rest for about half an hour.<br><br>
                 In a pan, place a little oil and fry the previously deveined guajillo chilies, just until they change color a little 
                 and the onions and garlic until they turn brown and soften. Place the above in the blender, along with the vinegar, 
                 the orange juice, the marinade and the oregano, then blend perfectly until all the ingredients are disintegrated.<br><br>
                 Pour the mixture over the meat and stir well, until all the meat is covered. Finally, let it rest again for 30 minutes in a refrigerator.<br><br>
                 In a clean pan, add a little oil and fry the meat, stirring constantly. When the meat is 3/4 of its cooking, add the pineapple in small cubes
                  and the filleted onion, until the meat is perfectly cooked.</p>
               
